title: Independent candidate Abdul Ghani wins PK-71 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Abdul Ghani won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-71, Khyber-III by securing 15,061 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamat-e-Islami Pakistan candidate Khan Wali who bagged 7,903 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turnout remained 18.18 per cent.
